name: Misfits
overview: When five young outsiders on Community Service get caught in a strange storm, they discover that they have developed superpowers.

seasons.name: Series 1
seasons.overview: Five unruly teenagers forced into community service to atone for their crimes develop superhero powers when a freak electrical storm hits them.

seasons.name: Series 2
seasons.overview: Nathan, Kelly and the gang discover that they're not the only ones affected by the storm as they now face a whole new world of weird characters.

seasons.name: Series 3
seasons.overview: New kid Rudy joins the gang of superpower-wielding kids this season. Meanwhile, the original misfits deal with some brand-new powers.

seasons.name: Series 4
seasons.overview: While new member Finn searches for his father, fellow newcomer Jess starts dating a guy who is searching for a missing piece of his anatomy.

seasons.name: Series 5
seasons.overview: As the first anniversary of the storm approaches, the Misfits fulfill their community service, ultimately pitting them against someone among them.

episodes.name: Episode One
episodes.overview: A group of misfits with nothing in common must perform community service, but get caught in a freak storm that gives them superpowers.

episodes.name: Episode Two
episodes.overview: Nathan is desperate to move back home, and when the group makes a discovery, he soon realizes he might have found his opportunity.

episodes.name: Episode Three
episodes.overview: Alisha is having fun using and abusing her powers but she can't seem to get the one man she really wants: Curtis.

episodes.name: Episode Four
episodes.overview: Curtis regrets the night of his arrest and uses his new power to travel back in time to change history, but it's not as easy as he thought.

episodes.name: Episode Five
episodes.overview: Determined to prove that the gang was involved in Tony's disappearance, Sally focuses her investigation on Simon.

episodes.name: Episode Six
episodes.overview: The gang realizes that there's something weird going on in town and it looks like the mysterious, straightlaced "Virtue" organization is behind it.

1.name: Series 1
1.overview: Five unruly teenagers forced into community service to atone for their crimes develop superhero powers when a freak electrical storm hits them.

episodes.name: Episode One
episodes.overview: A new probation officer assigns the group to an art class for the mentally ill. A mysterious hooded figure follows the Misfits for unknown reasons.

episodes.name: Episode Two
episodes.overview: Nathan is shocked when Jamie, a long-lost brother he never knew he had, turns up at the community center.

episodes.name: Episode Three
episodes.overview: The masked man saves Alisha from a mugging on the estate. It appears he is able to touch her without being affected by her powers.

episodes.name: Episode Four
episodes.overview: Ollie, an environmental protester who has the power to teleport, starts his community service. But is he really destined to become part of the gang?

episodes.name: Episode Five
episodes.overview: Nathan is violently killed again, and he suspects that Jessica, a charity worker from the community center, is to blame.

episodes.name: Episode Six
episodes.overview: After their superpowers are exposed to the world at large, the gang becomes celebrity superheroes, known as the ASBO Five.

episodes.name: Episode Seven
episodes.overview: Just before Christmas, the gang meets Seth, a drug dealer who was also struck in the storm and now has the ability to deal powers.

2.name: Series 2
2.overview: Nathan, Kelly and the gang discover that they're not the only ones affected by the storm as they now face a whole new world of weird characters.

episodes.name: Episode One
episodes.overview: New boy Rudy gets a rude awakening in his first few days of community service.

episodes.name: Episode Two
episodes.overview: Curtis decides to use his new gender-swap power so that he can return to athletics.

episodes.name: Episode Three
episodes.overview: Simon saves Peter, a geeky comic book nerd, from being mugged.

episodes.name: Episode Four
episodes.overview: An old Jewish man plans to use Curtis's power to go back in time and kill Hitler.

episodes.name: Episode Five
episodes.overview: Kelly gets trapped in the body of Jen, a coma victim, and the gang has to save her.

episodes.name: Episode Six
episodes.overview: Rudy discovers that he has contracted a strange superpower infection.

episodes.name: Episode Seven
episodes.overview: The gang battles an army of zombie cheerleaders when Seth resurrects his dead girlfriend.

episodes.name: Episode Eight
episodes.overview: A fake medium brings some dangerous deceased faces from the past back to life.

3.name: Series 3
3.overview: New kid Rudy joins the gang of superpower-wielding kids this season. Meanwhile, the original misfits deal with some brand-new powers.

episodes.name: Episode One
episodes.overview: New members Finn and Jess are zipping up for their first day of community service, but things get strange when a man stumbles in with a briefcase.

episodes.name: Episode Two
episodes.overview: Finn isn't quite as innocent as he looks when a dark secret he's been hiding at home is revealed.

episodes.name: Episode Three
episodes.overview: Rudy and his downbeat doppelganger are forced to unite as they have to confront a long-forgotten face from their shared past.

episodes.name: Episode Four
episodes.overview: Curtis learns his girlfriend is not the person she claimed to be. As he investigates further, he's forced to use his powers to revive a dead person.

episodes.name: Episode Five
episodes.overview: Finn tracks down his real dad and learns the man is dying. Finn's half-sister may know more about their father's illness than she's letting on.

episodes.name: Episode Six
episodes.overview: The gang goes to a party where they are stalked by a mysterious killer rabbit. While tracking it down, Rudy falls head over heels for the first time.

episodes.name: Episode Seven
episodes.overview: Alex sets off on a mission to try to recover what's missing in his life, but Jess is worried about the extreme lengths he might go to.

episodes.name: Episode Eight
episodes.overview: Rudy's passion for Nadine is put to the test when he tries to persuade her that they have a future together.

4.name: Series 4
4.overview: While new member Finn searches for his father, fellow newcomer Jess starts dating a guy who is searching for a missing piece of his anatomy.

episodes.name: Episode One
episodes.overview: The gang discovers a superpower support group and a group of Devil-worshipping scouts.

episodes.name: Episode Two
episodes.overview: Rudy sees his father with another woman. Jess helps Rudy investigate his dad and uncovers an even deeper secret.

episodes.name: Episode Three
episodes.overview: Sam, the mysterious flying boy from the future jumper, saves Dark Rudy from a mugger.

episodes.name: Episode Four
episodes.overview: The gang encounter Helen, an electrician who has a power that may explain the predictions of the mysterious knitted jumper.

episodes.name: Episode Five
episodes.overview: To help him get over Jess, Rudy takes Finn to the superpower support group, where a girl becomes infatuated with him.

episodes.name: Episode Six
episodes.overview: The gang realizes a terminally ill patient seems intent on cheating death, while Dark Rudy gets closer to finding the remaining hero on the jumper.

episodes.name: Episode Seven
episodes.overview: As the first anniversary of the storm approaches, the gang tries to celebrate. Alex discovers an unexpected side effect of his power.

episodes.name: Episode Eight
episodes.overview: The gang's community service is over and they are forced to face the future, while Dark Rudy finds that his new group isn't quite what he expected.

5.name: Series 5
5.overview: As the first anniversary of the storm approaches, the Misfits fulfill their community service, ultimately pitting them against someone among them.
